        <em>
          Ancient Mesopotamia
        </em>
         (1964). The principal new feature of this edition is the recalculation of late-second-millennium dates deriving from the Middle Assyrian lunar calendar and the corresponding recalibration of synchronistic Babylonian dates, which were based on a lunar-solar calendar, including their relationship with a set of known intercalary months from the fourteenth and thirteenth centuries. This presentation reflects research current in January 2023.
